column5: You & your buds always seem to have them dialed in Dave !!
Great report, Dave. Nothing like a little adventure with good buds.

Wonderful Dave. Perch are not hitting like before the heat wave and east winds here at Nanticoke either. Got many dinks yesterday and a few over 9". 1 former Stelco guy with me yesterday did get a beauty at 14"s. Should be 20 over 9". Love those big Erie Pickerel though, don't want any fish just leave me the cheeks please.  All we talked about was prescription medicine, I'll see your 500 milligrams of Crestor and raise you 1000 milligrams of Metformin! Used to be Sex, Drugs and Rock and Roll!
Some great eyes Dave.  I hope in 40 years I'm still sharing the boat with friends, beating on walleyes and sharing old stories.
Looks like some good eating there Dave... Congratulations!
Nice report buddy. Old boyz fishing trip,fish,brews and friendship. Good times.
Nice looking fish there Dave.  The plastic sliders u sold me are installed ready to go.  Haven't launched it yet to try them out.
Thanks everyone for the replys and kind words.
beauties.  what do you find in their bellies.  perch, smelt, gobies, shiners?
I didn't check, most likely they eat smelt & shinners
Thanks Brian. So far I like mine, launches and loads with ease. Hope to see you at Mohawk. Going to Hastings with a few Buds on Sat.
